       <div class="content-container">
            <!-- Left Image -->
            <img src="C:/Users/allic/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots/Screenshot 2025-05-08 141507.png" 
			alt="Original Map"
			class="larger-image">
			<!-- Center Text -->
            <div>
                <a href="https://arcg.is/1DH1CP0">
                    Hiking Survey
                </a>
                <p>
                    For this production I decided to make a survey that could track the most popular hiking spots. The goal was to understand what major demographics were hiking in certain areas and when. 
					The survey asks where the people hiked, who they were accompanied by, what time it was, and what level of schooling they were in i.e highschool, college, done/not in college. 
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    These surveys are then added to my feature layer in ArcGIS (picture below), where I can see where observations might start clustering. Because this was done at the end of the semester I made
					a few mock survey answers so that there were some observations to see on the map. 
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    Again, the main goal is to be able to visualize if there are any hiking hotspots in the area. 
                </p>
				<a href="https://umass-amherst.maps.arcgis.com/apps/mapviewer/index.html?layers=57b84547876b40059395b8f5eae4b1fc">
					Hiking Survey Map
				</a>
